================================================================================
Third-party dependencies
================================================================================

canvas-drop's runtime application image bundles its npm production dependencies
(the pruned node_modules of @canvas-drop/server and its workspace packages).
Every bundled production dependency is under a permissive, MIT-compatible
license. As of the latest audit, the production dependency tree (147 packages)
breaks down as:

    MIT            87
    Apache-2.0     48
    ISC             8
    BSD-3-Clause    3
    BSD-2-Clause    1
    0BSD            1
    MIT OR WTFPL    1

No copyleft (GPL/LGPL/MPL/EUPL/CDDL) licenses are present. Apache-2.0 components
are redistributed under the terms of that license; this NOTICE preserves their
attribution requirement.

Reproduce this inventory at any time with:

    pnpm --filter @canvas-drop/server licenses list --prod

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Redistribution boundary
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This NOTICE covers the npm dependencies bundled into the canvas-drop application
image. It does NOT cover the off-the-shelf container images that docker-compose
references and pulls at runtime — Dex, oauth2-proxy, Caddy, PostgreSQL, MinIO,
and the node:24-slim base image. Those are pulled from their own registries
under their own licenses and are not redistributed by this project.
